WEBVTT

00:00.959 --> 00:02.460
ANDY: <i>Previously on</i> NYPD Blue...

00:02.794 --> 00:06.131
Did you believe Lieutenant Rodriguez
intended to kill you?

00:06.339 --> 00:08.174
I had no doubt. He stood up,

00:08.258 --> 00:10.010
said it was me and him
alone in that office.

00:10.218 --> 00:12.929
He went for his gun.
Next thing I know, I'm shot in the back.

00:13.096 --> 00:14.639
VALERIE: Did you move towards him
at any time?

00:14.764 --> 00:16.891
No, I never came out from behind my desk.

00:17.100 --> 00:20.395
-Reach for your gun at any time?
-Absolutely not.

00:20.645 --> 00:23.606
It all comes down
to who you want to believe.

00:23.982 --> 00:27.694
A cop who's been the target
of investigations involving corruption,

00:27.861 --> 00:32.198
or a cop who has spent his entire career
protecting our city.

00:32.365 --> 00:35.285
Captain Fraker walked
into Lieutenant Rodriguez's office,

00:35.744 --> 00:41.833
and unprovoked, shot him.
I ask you to find Captain Fraker guilty.

00:42.500 --> 00:46.921
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)

00:59.893 --> 01:00.935
JOHN JR.: Dump job?

01:01.603 --> 01:03.021
Yeah.

01:03.104 --> 01:05.690
So, no word yet on the verdict
for the lieutenant.

01:06.107 --> 01:07.650
It's eight o'clock, Medavoy.

01:07.984 --> 01:09.861
Yeah, that's what I'm saying,
there's no word yet.

01:10.028 --> 01:11.905
-It was a statement.
-No, it wasn't.

01:11.988 --> 01:14.824
You wanna talk about it.
You're looking to start a conversation.

01:14.908 --> 01:17.368
But there isn't one to have
since it's 8:00 a.m.

01:17.786 --> 01:20.789
You know what?
Let's just stop this now and start over.

01:22.207 --> 01:26.628
Yes, John, there is a dump job
by a shopping cart down by the water.

01:26.836 --> 01:29.214
-Any ID yet?
-I'd have said so.

01:29.756 --> 01:32.509
There's bruises on her neck.
Looks like she's been knocked around.

01:32.592 --> 01:34.385
There's no shoes, no makeup, no purse,

01:34.719 --> 01:38.014
-I don't think she planned on going out.
-Who's the guy in the banana sling?

01:38.306 --> 01:39.808
BALDWIN: Uh, he's a swimmer.
Found the body.

01:39.891 --> 01:40.934
ANDY: Talk to him yet?

01:41.184 --> 01:44.187
I was kinda waiting for his suit
to lose the see-through aspect.

01:44.270 --> 01:45.480
But, hey, be my guest.

01:45.563 --> 01:47.107
JOHN JR.: People actually swim in there?

01:47.565 --> 01:49.859
This cart's from a grocery store
four blocks away.

01:49.943 --> 01:53.279
That means nothing.
I seen bums push them carts to Brooklyn

01:53.363 --> 01:57.033
-and back till the wheels fell off.
-Anyways, let's get back to work.

01:57.158 --> 01:59.202
Don't wanna have a personal conversation
here or nothing.

01:59.410 --> 02:02.122
(SCOFFS) All right.
Try and get some prints off her

02:02.205 --> 02:04.165
and whoever else
might have been pushing that cart.

02:04.249 --> 02:06.334
Let's go talk to Johnny Weissmuller
over here.

02:06.793 --> 02:08.419
(GRUNTS)

02:09.212 --> 02:11.047
-ANDY: <i>Ay, ay, ay.</i>
-Wally Moring.

02:11.256 --> 02:13.049
When was the last time
you had a tetanus shot, Wally?

02:13.133 --> 02:16.136
Uh, a couple of months ago.
Hepatitis A too, so I'm good.

02:16.386 --> 02:18.263
I'm training
for the Manhattan Island Marathon,

02:18.346 --> 02:21.057
just getting used to the water chop,
and the flotsam, and stuff.

02:21.141 --> 02:23.351
Hey, can we get somebody
to put something on this guy,

02:23.434 --> 02:24.978
a blanket or somethin'?

02:25.770 --> 02:26.938
How'd you find her, Wally?

02:27.063 --> 02:29.190
She was just there
when I got out of the water.

02:29.357 --> 02:31.526
-You were here yesterday too?
-Every morning this week.

02:31.860 --> 02:33.570
She... she wasn't here yesterday.

02:34.445 --> 02:35.738
-(KEYS CLANGING)
-Oh...

02:38.908 --> 02:39.909
Uncle.

02:42.787 --> 02:44.747
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

03:43.223 --> 03:45.016
(MUSIC CONCLUDES)

03:59.989 --> 04:01.908
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

04:02.116 --> 04:03.493
-You up?
-Yeah.

04:04.035 --> 04:08.665
Another dump job, white female. Get on it.
Where are we on that waterfront DOA?

04:08.748 --> 04:12.794
Just got her ID'd. Janelle Woodruff,
a few minor busts for possession.

04:13.002 --> 04:15.213
-Anything off the shopping cart?
-GREG: Nothing so far.

04:15.296 --> 04:17.298
Yeah, Crime Scene's still checking
for prints.

04:17.423 --> 04:19.342
-TONY: No witnesses?
-Nothing solid.

04:19.926 --> 04:22.053
We'll head over
to the DOA's apartment now.

04:22.553 --> 04:25.431
Uh, boss, do you, uh...
do you have a street on this?

04:25.765 --> 04:27.350
-It's on there.
-No, there's just a number.

04:29.519 --> 04:31.396
(PAPER RUSTLING)

04:31.896 --> 04:33.147
St. Mark's.

04:34.357 --> 04:36.859
I'll double-check, though.
If it's not, I'll get you on the radio.

04:36.943 --> 04:38.027
Thanks.

04:41.906 --> 04:45.326
(CLEARS THROAT)
The jury could be deliberating for days.

04:45.785 --> 04:47.287
They might even go
through the whole weekend.

04:47.370 --> 04:50.331
So, let's just put that aside
and get on with our business.

04:52.834 --> 04:53.960
(DOOR SLAMMING)

04:55.003 --> 04:56.504
You heard the man.

05:07.765 --> 05:09.225
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

05:09.309 --> 05:11.602
White female in the weeds.
Looks like she was strangled.

05:11.811 --> 05:12.812
Is that her bag?

05:13.146 --> 05:15.356
Still fishing for ID in this black hole.

05:15.940 --> 05:17.317
Queen of cosmetics in here.

05:17.734 --> 05:19.360
She didn't walk in this lot
in those heels.

05:19.861 --> 05:22.363
-CONNIE: Knees scraped up?
-Uh, no.

05:23.531 --> 05:24.991
No, she wasn't dragged very far.

05:25.491 --> 05:27.035
Maybe from the curb.

05:27.243 --> 05:28.494
Manual strangulation.

05:29.412 --> 05:31.039
No underwear, high heels.

05:32.165 --> 05:33.166
But no tracks.

05:33.791 --> 05:35.168
Nice hair, teeth.

05:35.710 --> 05:38.171
-So, it's too nice for a working girl.
-Yeah.

05:38.463 --> 05:39.464
Got the wallet.

05:40.673 --> 05:41.841
Eve Berlay.

05:41.924 --> 05:44.218
-Riverdale address, 40 years old.
-Really?

05:44.427 --> 05:48.473
-Two kids, lots of photos.
-What's she doing all the way down here?

05:48.556 --> 05:51.476
Well, whoever did this
left all her cash, credit cards.

05:51.559 --> 05:53.102
Jewelry, too. Look at this.

05:53.936 --> 05:55.104
"WWJD."

05:55.813 --> 05:57.607
-"What would Jesus do?"
-Yeah.

05:58.024 --> 06:00.234
Maybe it's "What would Jesus drink?"

06:00.693 --> 06:03.488
I've seen the t-shirts,
bearded guy in sandals on a Harley

06:03.654 --> 06:05.698
holding a couple of different bottles
of booze in his hands.

06:05.823 --> 06:08.868
Haven't seen the shirt.
I'll make sure they get on the rape kit.

06:10.787 --> 06:12.121
What would Jesus drink?

06:12.497 --> 06:15.333
-Come on, that's funny.
-Yeah, all right, we got it.

06:16.959 --> 06:20.129
-Fifteenth squad to Central K.
-DISPATCHER: <i>Go ahead, 15th Squad.</i>

06:24.801 --> 06:27.095
-Nothing.
-Yeah. Let's start a canvass.

06:31.307 --> 06:33.601
-(DOOR KNOCKING)
-JOHN JR.: NYPD!

06:36.187 --> 06:39.399
-Oh, sorry.
-Uh... no, it's no problem.

06:39.524 --> 06:42.693
Uh, did you... did you know your neighbor
Janelle Woodruff?

06:42.777 --> 06:43.861
Not really.

06:44.529 --> 06:47.323
-I heard she died.
-JOHN JR.: Yeah, unfortunately.

06:47.573 --> 06:50.701
Um, we're trying... (CHUCKLES) I'm sorry.

06:50.910 --> 06:55.164
Uh, my name is Detective Clark.
This is my partner, Detective Sipowicz.

06:55.248 --> 06:56.332
-Hi.
-ANDY: How's it going?

06:56.457 --> 06:58.501
-And your name?
-Marlissa Diaz.

06:58.626 --> 06:59.710
Marlissa, hi.

06:59.961 --> 07:02.797
Uh, so, what we need
is to get into Janelle's apartment.

07:02.880 --> 07:05.633
I don't have a key.
I really didn't talk to her much.

07:06.092 --> 07:09.887
Do you know anybody else who does
have a key, I mean, to her apartment?

07:10.263 --> 07:14.058
-No, she really kept to herself.
-Is there a super in the building?

07:14.392 --> 07:17.145
I haven't seen him.
But I just moved here a month ago.

07:17.228 --> 07:19.772
-That right? Uh, where you from?
-Philadelphia.

07:19.939 --> 07:24.068
-Yeah? That's great.
-My nephew's a big Sixers fan.

07:24.652 --> 07:27.989
(CHUCKLES) You might want
to try Janelle's son, Michael.

07:28.156 --> 07:30.032
-How old's Michael?
-Thirteen.

07:30.283 --> 07:31.451
Oh, he in school?

07:31.534 --> 07:32.827
MARLISSA: No, I usually see him
hanging out

07:32.910 --> 07:35.121
at the basketball courts
off of Catherine Street.

07:35.288 --> 07:37.373
He sells bottles of water out of a bag.

07:37.498 --> 07:40.334
Medavoy, why don't you and Jones
go ahead and take that?

07:40.543 --> 07:42.378
Okay. A couple of quick questions.

07:42.462 --> 07:46.632
Does... does he sell water only,
or does he maybe sell sodas?

07:46.716 --> 07:48.217
-Greg?
-What?

07:53.473 --> 07:57.018
-Anything else you can think of?
-No. (CHUCKLES) I'm sorry.

08:00.271 --> 08:01.772
Can I go back inside now?

08:01.856 --> 08:03.149
-Sure.
-Absolutely. Yeah.

08:08.863 --> 08:09.906
I love her.

08:11.908 --> 08:12.909
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

08:12.992 --> 08:15.328
We're sorry again about your wife,
Mr. Berlay.

08:15.411 --> 08:17.872
I don't get this.
None of it makes any sense.

08:18.789 --> 08:21.792
Well, uh, we're here to help
figure it out, Mr. Berlay.

08:23.085 --> 08:26.172
But to do that, we need to ask you
some tough questions about your wife.

08:27.215 --> 08:31.427
(SIGHS) She worked at a cosmetic counter.
She was a wonderful mother.

08:31.677 --> 08:33.012
I don't know what else to tell you.

08:33.137 --> 08:35.932
-Has she been acting any different lately?
-No.

08:36.015 --> 08:39.060
-Getting any strange phone calls?
-No.

08:39.352 --> 08:41.229
CONNIE: Were any of her habits
different than usual,

08:41.395 --> 08:44.482
-what time she left for work or came home?
-What does that mean?

08:44.941 --> 08:46.734
Are you telling me
my wife was having an affair?

08:46.817 --> 08:50.029
-Because if you are, lay it out.
-Is that a possibility?

08:50.196 --> 08:52.740
Hell, no, and you can go to hell
for thinking it.

08:52.907 --> 08:54.617
Maybe we should take a few minutes.

08:54.784 --> 08:57.912
She wasn't having an affair,
at least that I knew of.

08:58.412 --> 09:00.998
-Was anyone bothering her?
-I don't know.

09:01.290 --> 09:04.210
No, once, there was this guy
in housewares

09:04.293 --> 09:06.504
who put a move on her,
but she backed him off.

09:06.587 --> 09:09.715
-She mention his name?
-George something. It was a while ago.

09:10.007 --> 09:12.093
-How long?
-Two years.

09:12.176 --> 09:15.388
-She said he moved to St. Paul.
-Just so we can rule you out,

09:15.721 --> 09:17.265
can you tell us
where you were this morning?

09:17.848 --> 09:22.562
I was with a client... Daniel Kawamoto,
looking at rental property.

09:23.729 --> 09:25.398
And everything was all right at home?

09:26.274 --> 09:27.358
Yes.

09:28.150 --> 09:30.945
What, now, I was stepping out on her,
that's where you're going next?

09:32.613 --> 09:35.199
Eve is the most beautiful woman
I've ever seen.

09:35.575 --> 09:38.953
That she would give me the time of day,
let alone fall in love with me or...

09:40.705 --> 09:44.125
(SOBS) ...is a miracle. (SNIFFLING)

09:44.292 --> 09:47.336
I'm sorry. I can't understand any of this.

09:58.306 --> 10:00.349
-Go ahead and take this.
-Yeah.

10:00.641 --> 10:02.226
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

10:03.144 --> 10:05.938
Hey, man, she swore up and down
that she was 18.

10:07.189 --> 10:08.941
(CHUCKLES) I'm just playing with you.

10:09.275 --> 10:11.027
Hey, we're looking for a kid
named Michael Woodruff.

10:11.110 --> 10:14.739
-We heard he hangs out here.
-Yeah, but I ain't seen him. not all day.

10:15.072 --> 10:16.574
Sells bottles of water, sodas.

10:16.782 --> 10:19.493
Sounds right, but like I said,
I ain't seen him.

10:20.202 --> 10:22.747
Y'all got a card?
I could give y'all a buzz if he shows.

10:22.872 --> 10:24.624
Well, whose bag of drinks is that then?

10:25.833 --> 10:27.168
-MALE VOICE: Don't know.
-Hey, what's your name?

10:27.627 --> 10:29.629
-Darryl.
-Am I getting messed with here, Darryl?

10:29.795 --> 10:32.048
I don't know whose bag that is.
And I don't know where Michael is.

10:32.173 --> 10:33.591
Nobody's messing with you.

10:33.799 --> 10:37.386
Look, you covering for him?
That would indicate that you like the kid,

10:37.470 --> 10:40.348
meaning I don't think
you want to see us chase him down,

10:40.431 --> 10:43.726
-which we're gonna have to do.
-His moms just got killed last night.

10:44.060 --> 10:46.479
-That's why we need to talk to him.
-He's scared, man.

10:46.687 --> 10:49.231
-We understand that.
-Now, he's got nobody else.

10:49.440 --> 10:52.568
-We'll treat him right. You got my word.
-Heard that before.

10:54.987 --> 10:56.447
Yo, Michael, come on.

11:05.414 --> 11:07.208
They gotta talk to you about your moms.

11:08.209 --> 11:09.710
I'm gonna check on you, okay?

11:16.342 --> 11:17.802
Appreciate it.

11:29.522 --> 11:32.024
(TELEPHONE RINGING IN DISTANCE)

11:34.276 --> 11:35.653
JOHN: Fifteenth squad.

11:40.032 --> 11:42.410
Lieutenant Rodriguez. Hey, Valerie.

11:43.536 --> 11:46.580
Sure. absolutely. I'll be right down.

11:49.041 --> 11:50.084
(SIGHS)

11:57.216 --> 11:59.677
-Hey, Lieu.
-Contact me only if it's an emergency.

11:59.760 --> 12:00.845
JOHN: Certainly.

12:03.389 --> 12:05.057
-The verdict's in.
-Good luck.

12:07.309 --> 12:08.936
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

12:15.151 --> 12:16.235
Uh...

12:21.532 --> 12:24.034
Again... (SIGHS) ...we're sorry
about your mom, Michael.

12:25.369 --> 12:27.079
-Thanks.
-How'd you find out?

12:27.580 --> 12:30.708
Some old guy down the block said
they found her by the water.

12:32.084 --> 12:33.252
So, it's true then.

12:34.211 --> 12:36.130
Yeah. Yeah, we're sorry.

12:37.339 --> 12:39.091
-You know how she got there?
-No.

12:39.550 --> 12:42.636
-Was she having any problems with anybody?
-Not like she'd tell me.

12:42.762 --> 12:44.805
You seem like a pretty sharp kid, Michael.

12:47.391 --> 12:50.102
-Maybe dealers.
-When's the last time you saw your mom?

12:50.853 --> 12:54.815
Yesterday, before she went out.
She got a call, and she had to leave.

12:55.107 --> 12:58.152
-You know where she went?
-I didn't ask. She didn't say.

12:58.694 --> 13:00.654
And you don't know
who she was talking to on the phone?

13:01.197 --> 13:03.324
-Maybe her boyfriend.
-And who's that?

13:03.783 --> 13:05.284
This fat dude named Desmond.

13:05.576 --> 13:07.703
He gets her high
so she'll hang out with him.

13:07.870 --> 13:10.873
What's his last name?
And where can we find him?

13:11.290 --> 13:14.627
Carter. He owns this car shop
on Great Jones Street.

13:15.878 --> 13:17.922
All right, I'll get Andy and John on that.

13:19.590 --> 13:21.717
You have anyone else you could stay with
for a while?

13:21.884 --> 13:24.762
-A family member or friend?
-I'm all right on my own.

13:24.845 --> 13:26.972
All right. How about you stay here
for a little bit then?

13:27.056 --> 13:29.308
I'll get you something to eat
while they talk to Desmond.

13:29.975 --> 13:31.018
I'm not hungry.

13:31.811 --> 13:32.853
I'd rather leave.

13:33.145 --> 13:35.564
Well, hang out here for a little bit,
all right?

13:48.160 --> 13:49.829
-(INDISTINCT CHATTER)
-What's this guy's name?

13:49.995 --> 13:51.997
Desmond Carter. This is it.

13:52.122 --> 13:55.084
-(CAR HORNS HONKING IN DISTANCE)
-(DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE)

13:56.252 --> 13:57.795
ANDY: Police! Open up!

13:59.421 --> 14:01.799
Hey, Andy. It was open.

14:03.509 --> 14:06.053
Hey, Carter! Desmond Carter! Open up!

14:11.475 --> 14:12.935
Oh, that's a big dog.

14:13.477 --> 14:16.438
I mean, he's chained up,
and he's back a ways, but...

14:17.898 --> 14:20.234
All right. On three.

14:22.069 --> 14:23.529
One, two, three.

14:24.989 --> 14:26.574
-Stay, stay! Stay!
-Whoa, whoa!

14:26.657 --> 14:28.534
-Stay, stay! Stay!
-Whoa, whoa! Whoa!

14:28.659 --> 14:30.744
Police! Get your dog back
or he's horsemeat!

14:30.870 --> 14:32.204
-Don't hurt him!
-Get him back!

14:32.454 --> 14:34.415
-Get him back.
-Here! Pixie, Pixie, come on. Come on.

14:34.498 --> 14:36.584
-Pixie?
-Every time I see a pit bull like that,

14:36.667 --> 14:38.919
there's a needle-dick like him
on the other end of it.

14:39.003 --> 14:40.754
-ANDY: You Desmond Carter?
-Yeah.

14:40.963 --> 14:42.131
Come here.

14:42.506 --> 14:44.049
DESMOND: What...
what's the problem here, guys?

14:44.174 --> 14:45.885
Janelle Woodruff your girlfriend?

14:46.802 --> 14:47.803
Was. Why?

14:48.137 --> 14:49.763
-When did you break up?
-Couple days ago.

14:49.930 --> 14:52.057
Well, then we got something to talk about,
Desmond. Let's go.

14:52.141 --> 14:57.563
-Look. Her crazy ex-husband punched me.
-Well, we got a lot to talk about then.

14:57.813 --> 14:59.064
-Come on, let's go.
-Let's go.

14:59.148 --> 15:01.567
Well, let me lock my place up, man.

15:08.782 --> 15:11.118
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

15:24.798 --> 15:26.050
What are you looking at?

15:28.552 --> 15:29.637
You the cops?

15:29.887 --> 15:31.388
Detectives McDowell and Ortiz.

15:31.972 --> 15:33.974
I only got a minute. Manager's a twitch.

15:36.852 --> 15:39.188
On the phone earlier,
you said you knew Eve Berlay.

15:39.271 --> 15:40.814
Yeah. We were neighbors in L.A.

15:40.981 --> 15:43.692
-When's the last time you talked to her?
-Few years. She all right?

15:43.776 --> 15:47.237
A few years? She called you last week,
Norma. We got her cell records.

15:47.321 --> 15:50.074
Look, guys, if she's involved
in something, I got nothing to do with it.

15:50.157 --> 15:51.367
Then why are you lying to us?

15:51.450 --> 15:53.577
'Cause I don't go looking to get people
locked up.

15:53.702 --> 15:55.788
I've had friends put in the hospital
for doing that.

15:55.913 --> 15:58.415
Eve's dead.
We found her murdered this morning.

15:58.791 --> 15:59.917
Oh, my God.

16:00.459 --> 16:02.002
CONNIE: What did you talk about last week?

16:02.127 --> 16:03.128
I don't know.

16:03.295 --> 16:06.173
The weather, old times?
Norma, we're not leaving.

16:06.340 --> 16:09.218
Just caught up.
It had been a long time. Years.

16:09.301 --> 16:11.637
Well, get specific,
or we'll do this at the station house.

16:11.887 --> 16:13.681
She asked me a lot of questions
about the past.

16:13.764 --> 16:15.057
Did it ever catch up to me?

16:15.182 --> 16:16.976
But it doesn't,
because I never left the business.

16:17.601 --> 16:18.644
What business?

16:18.727 --> 16:21.855
-Dancing, touring, films.
-Porn films?

16:21.939 --> 16:24.608
Yeah, but like I said,
you gotta leave for it to catch up.

16:24.817 --> 16:27.903
-Why was Eve curious about that?
-She did some movies.

16:29.571 --> 16:32.491
She might be a soccer mom now,
but she wasn't in '85.

16:32.574 --> 16:34.785
And since then,
she's been keeping it under wraps?

16:34.868 --> 16:38.080
Ever since she left L.A., except
for the occasional phone call to me.

16:38.414 --> 16:39.832
She completely ditched that life.

16:39.915 --> 16:42.334
But she was calling you now
because it caught up with her?

16:42.584 --> 16:45.796
It sounded like some guy called
