I'm Detective Clark.
This is Detective Sipowicz.

31:25.300 --> 31:27.927
We're very sorry
about what happened to your mother.

31:29.012 --> 31:32.181
Now, we've also been investigating
your mom's murder.

31:32.390 --> 31:34.434
And the problem we got right now
is that...

31:35.101 --> 31:36.394
my partner and I have found stuff out

31:36.561 --> 31:38.771
that's different than what you're telling
the other detectives.

31:39.355 --> 31:42.191
-I ain't been lying.
-Let's just start fresh, okay?

31:42.650 --> 31:44.444
Whatever you said before,
don't worry about it.

31:44.611 --> 31:47.947
We're not gonna hold anything against you.
We got witnesses who say your dad

31:48.031 --> 31:50.408
was at you and your mom's apartment
last night.

31:50.742 --> 31:52.118
JOHN JR.: Now, I see you're putting
all this effort

31:52.201 --> 31:54.829
into trying to keep your story straight.
Just relax.

31:54.996 --> 31:56.956
Let it go. And tell us what happened.

31:57.415 --> 32:00.627
Okay, so, he was there last night.
Don't mean he killed her.

32:00.793 --> 32:02.670
Now, did your dad ask you to lie about it?

32:02.795 --> 32:05.632
No. I just knew you cops
would try to lay this on him

32:05.715 --> 32:07.008
if I told you he was there.

32:07.216 --> 32:10.803
We also got witnesses heard yelling
coming from your apartment last night.

32:11.179 --> 32:14.390
People are saying it sounded
like your mom and dad were arguing.

32:14.933 --> 32:18.770
Where's the other guy, Detective Jones?
He's who I been talking to.

32:19.103 --> 32:21.105
Were your parents arguing last night,
Michael?

32:21.481 --> 32:22.815
I don't know nothing about that.

32:22.982 --> 32:25.109
Oh, we think you do.
In fact, we're pretty sure you do.

32:25.652 --> 32:28.071
Michael, did your dad threaten you
if you said anything?

32:28.279 --> 32:29.364
Nope.

32:31.449 --> 32:33.952
-Did you like your mom?
-Hell, yeah, I did.

32:34.285 --> 32:36.162
Maybe you shouldn't ask
that question again.

32:36.245 --> 32:37.705
ANDY: Then why aren't you sticking up
for her, hmm?

32:38.039 --> 32:41.209
She stuck up for you all these years
a lot more than your dad did.

32:44.545 --> 32:47.548
(SIGHS) You know how we found her?

32:48.549 --> 32:50.718
And I'm sorry, but you need to hear this.

32:51.260 --> 32:53.888
Stuffed in a shopping cart,
her face all bloodied,

32:53.972 --> 32:56.933
-left there for the sea gulls.
-Okay, that's enough.

32:57.600 --> 32:58.601
I don't want to hear no more.

32:58.768 --> 33:01.396
You're trying to protect the guy
who took your mom away from you.

33:01.562 --> 33:04.273
-He's my dad.
-He hasn't been there your whole life.

33:04.565 --> 33:07.110
And I don't care what he promised
to try to keep you quiet,

33:07.276 --> 33:09.696
he ain't gonna be there
for you now either.

33:12.365 --> 33:13.408
He's my dad.

33:15.868 --> 33:16.869
All right.

33:18.079 --> 33:19.080
All right.

33:19.872 --> 33:21.541
(SHUTTER CLOSING)

33:21.749 --> 33:23.584
I have said it now three times.

33:23.668 --> 33:26.212
This morning,
I was home alone in my apartment.

33:26.295 --> 33:28.464
Now, please tell me,
what am I doing here?

33:28.548 --> 33:30.341
(SIGHS) You sure you don't know,
Mr. Grybowski?

33:30.425 --> 33:32.135
I didn't hurt anyone.

33:32.468 --> 33:34.637
Who said anything
about hurting someone?

33:34.721 --> 33:38.808
You said the name Stella Starr,
which I've never heard before.

33:38.891 --> 33:43.479
Then you're asking me where I've been.
So, obviously, she must have been... hurt.

33:44.814 --> 33:46.941
-You know, this is ridiculous.
-Mr. Grybowski,

33:47.358 --> 33:51.988
a friend of Stella Starr's, or Eve Berlay,
told us she agreed to meet you.

33:52.071 --> 33:53.406
That friend gave us your name.

33:53.489 --> 33:55.950
Now, we understand your reluctance
to be honest,

33:56.034 --> 33:57.493
seeing how you've been busted before

33:57.577 --> 33:59.954
for stalking your coworker,
but give us the truth.

34:00.204 --> 34:02.832
You and Eve met. She signed some photos.

34:02.915 --> 34:07.128
You shook hands, and parted ways.
Or we got no choice but to arrest you.

34:07.336 --> 34:09.881
We met at the Washington Square diner.
No big deal.

34:10.006 --> 34:11.132
You hunted her down on the Internet?

34:11.215 --> 34:14.302
-"Hunted her down." I did a Google search.
-(CONNIE LAUGHING)

34:14.552 --> 34:16.220
And she just agreed to see you.

34:16.637 --> 34:18.014
Fifteen years keeping a secret,

34:18.097 --> 34:20.558
-but you're a big fan, so, why not?
-Yeah, pretty much.

34:20.808 --> 34:23.895
'Cause Eve's friend will testify
that you threatened to tell her husband

34:23.978 --> 34:26.981
-if she didn't meet you.
-All I said to her was, "You've got fans,

34:27.065 --> 34:29.817
"people who appreciate your work.
You can't shut us out."

34:29.984 --> 34:31.861
So, she met me, signed some photos.

34:32.236 --> 34:34.238
-We were friends.
-Were friends.

34:35.281 --> 34:38.284
Are. You... you're twisting
everything around.

34:38.367 --> 34:42.747
This is a case that breaks our hearts,
‘cause Eve would still be alive

34:42.830 --> 34:44.832
if she just didn't listen
to some really stupid advice,

34:44.916 --> 34:46.876
which was to indulge
your jerk-off fantasy.

34:46.959 --> 34:48.377
-Hey!
-This is someone

34:48.544 --> 34:51.047
who got her life together,
and you had to destroy it

34:51.255 --> 34:54.050
'cause you just can't get laid
in the real world.

34:54.175 --> 34:56.594
-Up yours, lady.
-You threatened her.

34:56.761 --> 34:58.930
And you were the last person
she met before she died.

34:59.013 --> 35:00.389
That's enough to get your DNA,

35:00.473 --> 35:02.642
which will match up
to what you left on her dead body.

35:02.809 --> 35:05.561
CONNIE: And since we're past
you denying it, here's your choices.

35:05.645 --> 35:07.313
Say you had feelings
for this Stella Starr,

35:07.396 --> 35:08.856
maybe... maybe you loved her.

35:09.107 --> 35:10.733
And when she wouldn't accept
your advances,

35:10.817 --> 35:13.569
you lost it, that's ten years.
Or keep lying,

35:13.653 --> 35:16.030
and we'll say
you're an obsessive porn-freak asshole

35:16.114 --> 35:19.367
who destroyed a happy family
for no good reason, 25 years.

35:20.243 --> 35:22.245
Stand up and turn around.
You're under arrest.

35:22.453 --> 35:25.748
She slapped me. She attacked me in my car.
I had to save myself.

35:26.332 --> 35:27.375
Why did she attack you?

35:27.458 --> 35:29.335
She was talking like a doctor,
how I need help,

35:29.460 --> 35:30.461
and it's not right that I call her.

35:30.586 --> 35:32.046
-And then...
-You choked her.

35:32.130 --> 35:33.756
She never attacked you. That was a lie.

35:33.965 --> 35:36.092
When you think you know somebody,
and that you're communicating,

35:36.175 --> 35:39.303
-and then she just wants to break it off.
-Break off what?

35:39.512 --> 35:41.347
You didn't have a relationship with her.

35:41.430 --> 35:43.432
She met with you
'cause she was scared you'd ruin her life.

35:43.724 --> 35:45.143
I just wanted to be in her life,

35:45.226 --> 35:47.270
but she treated me like a psycho
with his dick in his hand.

35:47.645 --> 35:50.106
And that earned you the right
to rape her and kill her?

35:50.773 --> 35:53.109
What was so wrong about saying
that I had love for her?

35:53.192 --> 35:55.319
-That I thought we could be friends?
-Tom...

35:56.445 --> 35:59.490
did you rape and strangle Eve Berlay
this morning?

35:59.615 --> 36:02.160
That's what we need to know,
so we can start to help you.

36:08.583 --> 36:10.626
I guess, I did. Yes.

36:12.962 --> 36:14.172
But I didn't rape her.

36:15.006 --> 36:17.049
She was dead before we had sex.

36:29.937 --> 36:31.647
-ANDY: Here's where we're at, Craig.
-Yeah.

36:31.814 --> 36:33.357
We just got Michael something to eat,

36:33.441 --> 36:35.484
give him a chance to calm down,
stop crying.

36:35.693 --> 36:37.195
-CRAIG: Okay.
-He's already given us

36:37.278 --> 36:38.529
that you were at the apartment last night.

36:38.654 --> 36:40.781
He also gave us
that you and Janelle argued.

36:40.865 --> 36:43.784
-Don't know why he'd say that.
-I do. You killed his mom.

36:43.951 --> 36:46.621
-Wrong, flat-out.
-(SIGHS)

36:47.830 --> 36:50.875
-You fish at all, Craig?
-Once or twice.

36:51.125 --> 36:53.461
The hook is in. Michael's going.

36:53.669 --> 36:57.215
I just come down here
'cause I'm a father to a young boy myself.

36:57.423 --> 37:01.219
And I would not want him to experience
what I'm about to put your son through.

37:01.469 --> 37:03.012
This is your last chance.

37:03.596 --> 37:05.556
You stand up for your son, or I break him.

37:06.182 --> 37:07.183
Listen...

37:11.020 --> 37:12.355
I got no beef with you.

37:12.897 --> 37:17.068
And I know you're doing your job,
but will you try and understand something?

37:17.652 --> 37:19.820
-And I'm talking man-to-man here.
-Sure.

37:20.029 --> 37:22.073
I'm not addressing
what happened last night with Janelle

37:22.156 --> 37:23.783
'cause I wasn't there, and I don't know.

37:24.367 --> 37:27.495
But this whole thing...
it's a family matter.

37:27.787 --> 37:29.705
You killing your wife,
that's a family matter?

37:29.956 --> 37:32.083
Uh, uh, uh,
I ain't said nothing about that.

37:32.166 --> 37:35.586
'Cause once again, I wasn't there,
and I don't know.

37:36.045 --> 37:38.881
I'm just informing you
this is a family matter.

37:38.965 --> 37:41.425
Well, that's why they got
manslaughter statutes.

37:41.550 --> 37:44.470
If this is something that came out
of a family dispute,

37:44.553 --> 37:47.765
-we can work with that.
-It's gonna stay a family matter.

37:48.349 --> 37:50.810
And my boy,
he ain't gonna give you nothing.

37:51.477 --> 37:52.687
Fishhook or no fishhook.

37:54.897 --> 37:57.275
I will guarantee you one thing, Craig.

37:58.317 --> 38:01.696
I'm gonna put this case together,
no matter what.

38:02.863 --> 38:04.031
Can I go?

38:05.866 --> 38:07.910
Yeah... for now.

38:22.508 --> 38:23.718
-(DOOR KNOCKING)
-ANDY: Boss?

38:24.927 --> 38:26.679
Woodruff didn't go, so I had to kick him.

38:27.722 --> 38:29.307
-All right.
-Where's Michael?

38:29.724 --> 38:32.268
Uh, Jones is trying to get him placed
somewhere decent.

38:32.685 --> 38:36.105
If we're gonna clear this,
that kid's gonna have to flip on his dad.

38:36.397 --> 38:38.232
Yeah, uh, stay on top of it.

38:41.193 --> 38:43.821
Lieu, you can't let this verdict
weigh on you.

38:44.572 --> 38:47.533
It's another jury-screwing.
It's got nothing to do with the truth

38:47.616 --> 38:49.618
or how anyone around here
or anywhere else

38:49.702 --> 38:52.246
-feels about what happened.
-I know. I'm fine.

38:59.837 --> 39:03.549
I know you're all concerned about me,
and, um, I appreciate it.

39:04.008 --> 39:06.635
But just understand,
all this has been is a disappointment.

39:06.969 --> 39:09.930
I'm not worried about repercussions
or what anyone thinks.

39:10.139 --> 39:12.350
More than anything,
I'm just glad it's over.

39:12.641 --> 39:14.769
Good. Then it's put to bed.

39:15.478 --> 39:16.520
Right.

39:18.147 --> 39:20.608
So, goodnight, everyone.

39:21.442 --> 39:22.568
See you all tomorrow.

39:23.527 --> 39:25.321
-We'll start fresh.
-Night, boss.

39:26.364 --> 39:27.365
Goodnight.

39:28.199 --> 39:30.868
Hey! You sure you're all right?

39:31.494 --> 39:33.454
Positive. Thanks, though.

39:45.841 --> 39:47.760
All right. (SIGHS)

39:47.843 --> 39:50.429
My contact over at child services
is gonna call me back.

39:50.930 --> 39:52.139
I'll be fine on my own.

39:52.223 --> 39:53.933
-I keep telling you that.
-Doing what?

39:54.308 --> 39:58.354
-Selling bottles of water in the park?
-I'll work it out. I always have.

39:58.729 --> 40:01.941
Michael, this lady over at child services
is a friend of mine.

40:02.108 --> 40:03.692
I can get her to cut
through all the red tape

40:03.776 --> 40:05.611
and get you into a good foster home.

40:06.195 --> 40:07.279
Wouldn't you rather have that

40:07.363 --> 40:09.490
instead of spending the night
in the emergency center?

40:10.282 --> 40:13.244
-You don't need to do favors for me.
-Well, that's a yes-or-no question.

40:13.953 --> 40:16.872
Don't you want a nice place
to stay with good people?

40:17.373 --> 40:18.916
(SIGHS) I guess so.

40:19.041 --> 40:21.293
But the thing is, you gotta hold up
your end of the bargain.

40:21.502 --> 40:23.629
You gotta act right, or you'll get tossed.

40:24.463 --> 40:25.756
But I know you can do it.

40:26.799 --> 40:30.261
I got faith in you. Otherwise,
I wouldn't be calling in this favor.

40:30.678 --> 40:31.762
Yeah, okay.

40:32.513 --> 40:34.515
You're at a critical time in your life,
Michael.

40:34.765 --> 40:36.308
There's two ways you can go.

40:36.517 --> 40:39.311
Now, if you want to move forward
towards good things, I can help you.

40:40.354 --> 40:41.897
I'm not just talking about tonight.

40:42.857 --> 40:45.025
-What's the catch?
-There's no catch.

40:47.820 --> 40:50.781
-I'm not gonna rat out my dad.
-I'm not asking you to.

40:52.491 --> 40:53.659
And what's in it for you?

40:54.076 --> 40:56.745
When I was your age, I was in a bad spot.

40:58.122 --> 40:59.707
And somebody helped me out.

41:02.585 --> 41:03.752
Do you want my help?

41:05.671 --> 41:07.423
-Yeah.
-Okay.

41:11.969 --> 41:14.638
You know, it's all right to feel sad
about your mom.

41:15.222 --> 41:16.265
I'm all right.

41:16.682 --> 41:17.683
I'm just saying.

41:18.642 --> 41:21.395
Nobody here knows you,
and I'm not gonna judge you.

41:22.062 --> 41:23.689
So, if you want to talk about it, you can.

41:24.440 --> 41:27.401
(SNIFFLES) I'm just thinking, like...

41:29.361 --> 41:30.779
you know, how hard it's gonna be...

41:32.323 --> 41:33.741
waking up tomorrow and...

41:34.658 --> 41:36.452
(CHUCKLES) ...her not being around.

41:37.703 --> 41:38.787
I know.

41:40.539 --> 41:41.624
I'm sorry.

41:43.918 --> 41:44.919
(SNIFFLES)

41:45.252 --> 41:46.837
(MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING)

41:47.129 --> 41:48.464
It's gonna be all right.

41:49.673 --> 41:51.217
I'm gonna get you through this.

41:57.723 --> 42:00.142
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

42:31.715 --> 42:33.342
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

42:59.076 --> 43:00.786
